{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01KxhUseHwPUMbNu6dzSA6Hy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Using cylindrical coordinates with $r^2 = x^2+y^2$, the inequality becomes\n$$(r^2 + z^2 + 8)^2 \\le 36 r^2.$$\n\nSince the left side is nonnegative and we need the right side to dominate, taking square roots (with $r \\ge 0$):\n$$r^2 + z^2 + 8 \\le 6r,$$\nwhich rearranges to\n$$(r-3)^2 + z^2 \\le 1.$$\n\nIn the $(r,z)$ half-plane this is a disk of radius $1$ centered at $(3,0)$. Rotating it about the $z$-axis produces a torus with major radius $R=3$ and minor radius $a=1$.\n\nBy Pappus's theorem: $V = (\\pi a^2)(2\\pi R) = 2\\pi^2 R a^2 = 2\\pi^2 \\cdot 3 \\cdot 1 = 6\\pi^2$.\n\nANSWER: 6π²\nCONFIDENCE: high"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":476,"cache_read_input_tokens":19541,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":476},"output_tokens":59,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c05bdae8-2e4c-4fb6-ab47-7f6e1b6e14a2","uuid":"ed82a994-e593-410e-8e28-25fc72282f83","request_id":"req_011CbDRFLbw3DuPJqBFC8iJ3"}
